annotation_set.note:
DRAFT (pending ISBT approval). ---. Polymorphisms in LRG_802, SLC14A1 give rise to antigenic variants of the Kidd blood group system, JK (ISBT 009). These LRG reference sequences represent the JK01/A allele (haplotype) of the Kidd blood group system. ---. Previous reference literature (1,2) for blood group systems has used the JK02/B allele (haplotype) as the reference allele. This was represented in NM_015865.5 (NOTE VERSION NUMBER). NM_015865.5 was updated to NM_015865.6 to match the reference human genome (GRCh37/38) which represents JK01/A. The ISBT has agreed to switch the reference allele to JK01/A (NM_015865.6). This will be updated in future ISBT tables. ---. Reference literature (1, 2) for blood group systems which listed NM_015865 as the reference transcript also incorrectly described the model as an 11 exon model, with translation initiating in exon 4. NM_015865 is a 10 exon model, with translation initiating in exon 3. An 11 exon model that has an additional 3? UTR exon does exist (NM_001146036.2/ENST00000586951.6), however this transcript is minor compared to NM_015865.
.---. REFERENCES.
1) International Society for Blood Transfusion (ISBT) allele tables, JK (ISBT 009) v4.0 160705. http://www.isbtweb.org/working-parties/red-cell-immunogenetics-and-blood-group-terminology/ 2) The Blood Group Antigen FactsBook, 3rd Edition, Authors: Marion Reid, Christine Lomas-Francis, Martin Olsson
